I'm very proud to announce Webconverger 11, with the following improvements:

* [Firefox 9](http://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/9.0/releasenotes/)
* Ability to change [[browser_chrome|kiosk]] options at [[boot_time|boot]]!
* Quieter boots
* Several enhancements on the [Firefox Webconverger extension](https://github.com/kaihendry/iceweasel-webconverger), many thanks to [Mike Kaply](http://mike.kaply.com/)
* Security tweaks to make the [control script](http://git.webconverger.org/?p=webconverger-base;a=blob;f=home/webc/pb.sh;) harder to override
* New logo and [site design](http://webconverger.com/), [[thanks|acknowledgements]] [Patric](http://www.bureauschwarz.de)!
* Networking interface naming bug spotted by [Stewart](https://groups.google.com/forum/#!msg/webc-users/DHZaaeRXvwc/CfdpSCGLzhkJ) and fixed by [Matthijs Kooijman](https://groups.google.com/forum/#!msg/webc-users/DHZaaeRXvwc/cH63UBwGQOwJ)

